Caesar cipher is one of the oldest forms of classical ciphers. The quote from Shakespeare's play, "Julius Caesar", further nudges the individual in that direction. There are numerous tools online for automatically deciphering a caesar cipher, but they generally either rely on statistical analysis (i.e. The most common letter in the English language tends to be "e"), or they cycle through the 25 different possible combinations, looking for which shift value makes the best words.
